The paper discusses the design and implementation of proactive defense mechanisms to prevent attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and metrics to evaluate the effectiveness of these mechanisms, which falls under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of intelligent and adaptive techniques to prevent attacks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Lastly, the paper discusses the application of these mechanisms in various domains, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
